1
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:29,980
[The Vendetta of An]

2
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,930
♪Huainan is good♪

3
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:37,260
♪A safe haven♪

4
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:44,380
♪The mountains and rivers stretch on like our affection♪

5
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,930
♪Devoted souls dwell here♪

6
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:50,820
Huainan is indeed a fine place,

7
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,020
but we are no longer there.

8
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:56,490
Huai'an truly thinks ten steps ahead.

9
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:58,930
He even predicted matters of life and death in his letter.

10
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,090
You are too gentle by nature.

11
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,730
You are the one

12
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:12,780
I worry about most.

13
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,780
If you face something

14
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,220
you cannot overcome one day,

15
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,340
open this letter.

16
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,450
"Zhou Mo joined the Huben Army

17
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:28,730
and fell under their yoke.

18
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:31,450
Only death could free him.

19
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:33,850
Killing him

20
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,780
was to save him."

21
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:38,500
If I make it to the Capital alive,

22
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,980
they will hunt you

23
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,820
to the ends of the earth.

24
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:45,570
Only by dying once

25
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,980
can you truly be free.

26
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,820
[Zhou Mo joined the Huben Army and fell under their yoke.]

27
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:51,020
[Only death could free him.]

28
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:51,980
[Killing him was to save him.]

29
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,410
No, we are no longer in Huainan.

30
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,380
He should be in Chang'an by now.

31
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:12,380
The dangers of Chang'an

32
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,130
far surpass Huainan's.

33
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,090
I hope he stays safe.

34
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:20,290
He will be.

35
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:23,620
♪A devoted soul sings here♪

36
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:28,260
♪I brave the snow to see you off♪

37
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:33,060
♪I await your return, though my temples may turn to frost♪

38
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,260
♪My devotion endures as long as water flows♪

39
00:03:36,340 --> 00:03:39,300
[Episode 2]

40
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:49,940
[Yang Xuan, Vice Minister of Revenue]

41
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:52,180
[At dawn I rise]

42
00:03:52,420 --> 00:03:53,660
[Parting weighs on my mind]

43
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,740
[Bai Wan, Yang Xuan's student]

44
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:20,490
"Studying by the cold window, I never sensed how brief the seasons were.

45
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:27,340
In a blink, my temples have turned to gray frost.

46
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:28,580
[Rebel fire]

47
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:37,610
Schemes for the realm are but a dream.

48
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:45,930
I wake from wine to Hu horses trampling the land.

49
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:54,810
The loyal dead would never stain their bones with rebel fire,

50
00:04:57,430 --> 00:05:03,610
yet traitors crave the splendor of the august hall.

51
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:12,100
Half a life I spent on these texts. For whom were they written?

52
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:16,810
For whom, I ask?

53
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:25,980
Let this long lament be burned and offered to the mountain spirits.

54
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:34,900
Let this long lament be burned and offered to the mountain spirits!"

55
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:03,730
Sir!

56
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,140
Sir...

57
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,780
Sir?

58
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:35,700
Sir...

59
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:52,100
[Commander Wang]
Why are you guarding this traitor?

60
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,170
I was his student.

61
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,700
Now that he lies dead on the street,

62
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,170
please let me keep vigil

63
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,580
until the people from the Jingzhao Yamen

64
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,490
come to collect his body.

65
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,340
He was a traitor.

66
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,020
We of the Imperial Guards will take him.

67
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:19,250
You call yourself his student.

68
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:23,250
Are you a traitor too?

69
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:33,930
Sir,

70
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:35,850
this has nothing to do with us.

71
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,100
Please proceed.

72
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:42,610
It has nothing to do with you indeed.

73
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,700
Take her!

74
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:45,610
Stop.

75
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,610
In this bitter snow,

76
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:23,980
she is willing to keep vigil for this old man's body.

77
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:26,340
It is a righteous deed,

78
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,540
yet you call her a traitor?

79
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,460
Where is your proof?

80
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:44,980
I cannot stand scholars.

81
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,820
Are you looking

82
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,890
to light your own way to the grave?

83
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,220
You all heard him.

84
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:58,820
He tried to defend this traitor.

85
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:00,760
Take him too!

86
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,550
Hold!

87
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,340
Who dares bar the Imperial Guards?

88
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,770
Academician Li,

89
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,610
what brings you here?

90
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:15,420
You Imperial Guards

91
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,420
are bold indeed,

92
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,530
blocking anyone as you please.

93
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,300
Greetings, Mr. Huai'an.

94
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:22,890
Greetings, Academician Li.

95
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,060
His Majesty awaits you in the palace.

96
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,010
Please get in.

97
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:32,220
"Studying by the cold window, I never sensed how brief the seasons were.

98
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:34,460
In a blink, my temples have turned to gray frost.

99
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,770
Schemes for the realm are but a dream.

100
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,580
I wake from wine to Hu horses trampling the land.

101
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:42,850
The loyal dead would never stain their bones with rebel fire,

102
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:47,010
yet traitors crave the splendor of the august hall.

103
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,250
Half a life I spent on these texts. For whom were they written?

104
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,130
Let this long lament be burned and offered to the mountain spirits."

105
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:00,650
You called me a traitor

106
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,580
without a shred of proof.

107
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,130
I recited a seditious poem just now.

108
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,580
That gives you some proof.

109
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:09,220
Can you

110
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,850
confirm that I'm a traitor now?

111
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:16,530
You're silent.

112
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:18,770
Does that mean I am not?

113
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,340
If we've come to a point

114
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:23,340
where words alone

115
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,180
can convict someone of treason,

116
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:28,490
then heed my words:

117
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,250
you are a traitor.

118
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:34,850
You are a traitor.

119
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,420
You are a traitor!

120
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:41,850
Mr. Huai'an,

121
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,060
don't take his words to heart.

122
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,180
Academician Li,

123
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:53,850
I have one small request.

124
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:54,610
Of course.

125
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,130
Please leave them be.

126
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,300
No problem.

127
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:01,220
Get lost!

128
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:03,770
I take my leave.

129
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:06,700
Let's go!

130
00:11:08,030 --> 00:11:08,420
This way,

131
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:09,420
please.

132
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,250
Take this to shelter him

133
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:46,060
from the wind and snow.

134
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,250
Thank you.

135
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,220
Wan,

136
00:12:23,150 --> 00:12:24,770
there is something

137
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:25,980
I must tell you.

138
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,460
That article slandering the new emperor

139
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,010
was written by me.

140
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,980
I work for the Huben Army.

141
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:37,610
My rise

142
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:38,940
to this post

143
00:12:39,510 --> 00:12:41,130
was propped up

144
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,850
by them.

145
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,770
Everything I did

146
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:48,880
was at the Huben guards' command.

147
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:51,010
Now, I must let this frail body of mine

148
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,770
serve its final purpose

149
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,220
so they will

150
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:56,580
keep my family safe.

151
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,940
The Huben Army

152
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:01,130
once asked me about you.

153
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,820
After I die,

154
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,530
they will come for you.

155
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:08,650
I can only

156
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,300
give you one last warning:

157
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:15,250
never defy the Huben Army.

158
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,100
You still wish to see

159
00:13:17,670 --> 00:13:18,890
your family again, don't you?

160
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,420
Then do whatever it takes

161
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,010
to survive.

162
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:29,610
Sir...

163
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,850
Do not grieve for me.

164
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:37,610
Everyone

165
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:40,060
must walk the road

166
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,530
fate has set for them.

167
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,340
Rest now,

168
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:47,530
Wan.

169
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,980
This may be

170
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:55,530
your last peaceful sleep.

171
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,100
Tonight,

172
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:00,820
I will

173
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,650
take my life at the city gate

174
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,530
as an old minister

175
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,530
of the former court

176
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,460
to show my defiance of the new emperor.

177
00:14:11,670 --> 00:14:12,490
Yan Fengshan

178
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,220
commands the Huben Army

179
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,610
and held the court in his grip for years.

180
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,420
Xiao Wuyang seized Chang'an

181
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:22,010
to keep imperial power from slipping away.

182
00:14:23,670 --> 00:14:24,730
Though the Huben Army

183
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,610
has avoided meeting him head-on,

184
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,820
Yan Fengshan still intends

185
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,250
to set Chang'an aflame

186
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,300
and give Xiao Wuyang no peace.

187
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,180
And I

188
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:43,180
am a piece of wood they need for that fire.

189
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:28,890
Academician Li.

190
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:30,770
I hope you do not mind

191
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:32,980
that I used your hand to slap

192
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,650
the Imperial Guards in the face.

193
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,300
Not at all.

194
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:38,730
They

195
00:15:39,150 --> 00:15:39,890
deserved it.

196
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:42,100
I intended to humiliate that commander.

197
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,250
Even if you hadn't been there, sir,

198
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,530
I would have

199
00:15:46,030 --> 00:15:47,580
found another way

200
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:49,300
to shame him another day.

201
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:51,100
That is

202
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,250
how I handle matters.

203
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:11,890
Assassins!

204
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:12,820
Protect His Majesty!

205
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,130
Quick, protect His Majesty!

206
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:15,010
Understood!

207
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:16,530
Assassins!

208
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:19,940
Assassins! Protect His Majesty!

209
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:24,370
The realm is still unsettled.

210
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,610
It's been but a month since His Majesty took the throne,

211
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:27,980
and already

212
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,940
a dozen assassination attempts have been made.

213
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,890
No need to panic, though.

214
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,770
Under the Dingtang Sword,

215
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,850
all who come lose their heads.

216
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:48,660
Your subject,

217
00:17:49,030 --> 00:17:49,940
Xie Huai'an,

218
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,620
greets Your Majesty.

219
00:17:55,070 --> 00:17:55,980
Lift your head.

220
00:17:58,030 --> 00:17:59,220
I asked many people

221
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,140
who could seek someone for me

222
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,330
in this vast world.

223
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,660
They all

224
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,180
recommended you,

225
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,660
so I wished to see for myself

226
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,490
whether you are capable of the task.

227
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,700
These ten essays

228
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,570
were all written for the imperial examination

229
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,700
in the 11th year of the dynasty.

230
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,180
One of them was written by me.

231
00:18:21,590 --> 00:18:22,490
Find it.

232
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:23,730
As you

233
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:24,490
command.

234
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,340
[Benevolent Rule]

235
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:07,260
[He united the lords and steadied the realm, rising as the foremost hegemon]

236
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:08,540
[The Forceful Rule and the Benevolent Rule]

237
00:19:22,270 --> 00:19:23,420
Your Majesty, I have found

238
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:24,810
your essay.

239
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,180
It's only been half a stick of incense.

240
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,180
Even if you read ten lines at a glance,

241
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,250
you could only have finished three or four essays.

242
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,380
How did you manage it?

243
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:40,980
Southerners and northerners differ.

244
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:43,460
Their wording and phrasing leave traces.

245
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:44,940
Before Your Majesty turned 20,

246
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:45,980
you lived long in Chang'an.

247
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,140
Your early learning

248
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,250
came from Grand Secretary Bai Linian,

249
00:19:50,070 --> 00:19:51,250
who was from Wuyue.

250
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,010
Therefore,

251
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:54,940
Your Majesty's writing

252
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:56,660
shows southern traits.

253
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:59,220
Southerners write "lu" as "six,"

254
00:19:59,270 --> 00:20:01,420
"qi" as "stand," and "bei" as "cover."

255
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,460
Northerners write "chen" as "ugly,"

256
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:04,330
"geng" as "road,"

257
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,620
and "tong" as "reach."

258
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:07,530
By this measure,

259
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:08,530
seven of the essays

260
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,530
were written by northerners,

261
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:13,140
and only three by southerners.

262
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,730
Everyone has words and phrases

263
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,460
they tend to repeat.

264
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:18,900
"In troubled times,

265
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:20,380
hearts are easily disturbed,

266
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,940
so virtue alone cannot calm them."
